  "result": "1. Turn switch A on and leave it on for about 10 minutes.\n2. Turn switch A off.\n3. Turn switch B on.\n4. Immediately enter the room.\n5. The bulb that is lit is controlled by B.\n6. Touch each of the two unlit bulbs; the warm one is controlled by A, and the cool one is controlled by C.\n\nWhy this works: Each switch leaves a distinct, observable signature on its bulb at the moment of entry. B is the only switch currently powered, so its bulb is the lit one. A was powered long enough to heat its bulb but is now off, so its bulb is dark yet warm. C was never on, so its bulb is dark and cool. The three states (lit, warm-and-dark, cool-and-dark) uniquely identify all three switches in a single visit.",
